ble, aunque con ropajes siempre renovados, es la desigualdad material y simbólica. Aunque cada vez cuesta más hablar de el pueblo, lo que permanece es la jerarquización, la discriminación, la subalternidad - de clase, de etnia, de raza, de género-, la invisibilización, el silencio. Todos los espacios donde, tercamente, habla lo popular.  afunded by Universität Bielefeld  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPopular culturezLatin America. 4aBielefeld University Press. 4aCultura De Masas. 4aCultural Studies. 4aCulturas Plebeyas. 4aHibridación. 4aLateinamerika. 4aPopkultur. 4aSoziale Bewegungen. 4aSubalternidad. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aBielefeld University Press.  aCultural Studies.  aLatin America.  aSocial Movements.2 aUniversität Bielefeldefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839456422zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839456422zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839456422/original  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSLb2021  aZDB-23-GOA